With Wren Homecoming approaching i now more than ever miss our LED SIGN. There is no money in our budget for replacement, and the sign can no longer be repaired.
Do you know of an organization that might help us? Possible grant opportunities? Would you come to a bingo/fundraising event to raise money for a new sign? Estimated cost $12,000 - that‚Äôs the price for a basic sign - we don‚Äôt need all the bells and whistles.
The Van Wert County Foundation has been extremely generous with our Village - we cannot ask them for help with this sign.
Thank you in advance for your creative suggestions.

post_text:
Monica Davis

WREN ‚Äî The Wrenway Park Wiffleball Tourney Committee has announced that Wren Mayor Monica Davis will throw out the ceremonial first pitch for this year‚Äôs tournament. The festivities will begin at 5:45 p.m. Friday, August 17, at Wrenway Park, with the championship game taking place at approximately 9:30 p.m. Saturday.

Mayor Davis was chosen to throw out the first pitch for the 27th annual Wiffleball tournament not only because of her dedication to the village as mayor, but also her involvement in the organization and set-up of the tournament.

Davis and her husband, Wiffleball Commissioner Jack Davis, have three children and six grandchildren. Along with her mayoral and Wiffleball duties, she is a nurse and hospice volunteer.

In addition to selecting who will throw out the first tournament pitch, tournament organizers announce that Addy, Nora, and Marlee Vaughn, 17-year-old daughters of Andy and Jeanette Etzler and Aaron and Jill Vaughn, will be performing during the 27th annual Wrenway Park Wiffleball Warehouse pre-championship festivities.

post_text:
Voltz to sing National Anthem at tourney
VW independent/submitted information

Ivan Voltz

WREN ‚Äî As part of opening ceremonies for the Wiffleball Warehouse Tournament in Wren, local resident Ivan Voltz will be singing The National Anthem during opening ceremonies, starting at 5:50 p.m. Friday, August 17, at Wrenway Park.

Voltz was a Crestview bus driver for 30 years and also served in the United States Army in the Pacific as part of the occupation force in Japan just after World War II.

Other than his time in the military, Voltz has lived in the Wren area and is ‚Äúproud to have laid his head on his own pillow every night‚Äù.

Voltz has two adult children and five grandchildren. He attends Wren United Brethren Church.

The councilmembers and I would like to thank every resident that is helping make Wren such a great place to live.

Thank you for being good neighbors and looking out for one another.
Thank you for keeping your properties looking beautiful. We see you cleaning the street in front of your home. Thank you for that and, thank you for not blowing grass into the street when you mow.
Wren will have lots of company this weekend and thanks for helping us get the Village ready.

PS - If you have a vehicle that doesn‚Äôt run and/or is not currently plated it needs to be removed. Let us know how we can help.

Monica Davis

The Wren Christmas Society will be holding a Soup & Sandwich fundraiser on Sunday, April 8, from 11 a.m. until 1 p.m., at The Building in Wren.

The choice of soup will be chili or potato soup, while the choice of sandwich will be pulled pork or creamed chicken. There will be coffee, fruit punch, or water to drink, and cookies or brownies for dessert.

The cost will be by donation and carryout will be available.

The money raised will be used to add to the organization‚Äôs Christmas display and to replace light strands and bulbs. Direct any questions to Karen at 419.495.2623.

We are thankful for those who abide by the rules.

WREN CHRISTMAS SOCIETY NEWS

The Christmas Society put up decorations in Wren on Saturday, November 19th and the Grand Illumination will be held on Saturday, Nov. 26th at dark (approximately 6:00 pm).

The WCS held a "Create your own Christmas scene" contest for area children in grades K-5 for the chance to turn on the Christmas lights in Wren for the Grand Illumination. The winner of that contest was Jetta Merkle.

The Society will also be sponsoring an Outside Home Display Contest again this year within a 3-mile radius of Wren. Please contact Moe Davis at 419-495-2584 with any questions.

Santa and Mrs. Claus will be in Wren at the Santa House at the corner of St. Rt. 49 and Jackson Street on Saturday, December 10th and Friday and Saturday, December 16th and 17th from 6 to 8 pm. Carriage rides, hot chocolate and cookies will be available during Santa hours.

post_text:
The Board of Trustees of the Wren Community Chest met January 10, 2016 for the last meeting of the year. The Secretary reported that the inventory has been taken. Three Trustees were up for re-election. Jessica Heckler, Larry Lichtensteiger, and Rich Hire all accepted another three year term. Officers elected were Rich Hire-Chairman, Dede Strickler-Co-Chairman, Larry Davis-Sec.Treas., and Cheryl Mollenkopf-Co-Sec.Treas.
The yearly summary was gone over. Monetary donations have gone out to Crestview Scholarships, People in Need, Wren Ball Park, Wren Fire Dept, Wiffleball Warehouse, Crestview Academic Hall of Fame, Wren Homecoming Parade, Memorials, Crestview Football Parent Assoc.
We would like to thank all who have donated to the Wren Community Chest!
text:

Officers elected were Rich Hire-Chairman, Dede Strickler-Co-Chairman, Larry Davis-Sec.Treas., and Cheryl Mollenkopf-Co-Sec.Treas.
The yearly summary was gone over. Monetary donations have gone out to Crestview Scholarships, People in Need, Wren Ball Park, Wren Fire Dept, Wiffleball Warehouse, Crestview Academic Hall of Fame, Wren Homecoming Parade, Memorials, Crestview Football Parent Assoc.

Attention Village Residents

We are excited about, and gearing up for, Homecoming Weekend 8/20 ‚Äì 8/22 ‚Äì your property is a reflection of you. We are encouraging you to clean up your yard, mow and trim your property/properties. Please get rid of any vehicles on your property that do not run. If you have any questions you can contact the Mayor at 419-495-2752 or any councilperson ‚Äì if the vehicle does not run/cannot be driven it must be stored inside a building or removed from the Village. Letters will be mailed out the second week of July. There is no longer a warning on the letters, once it is mailed the Village will take necessary action to clean up your property or call the VW Sheriff regarding junk cars. Thank you for your cooperation with this matter. We all want to keep our Village looking great.

This is also a perfect time to thank you for not blowing your mown grass into the street and for not burning trash ‚Äì as per the EPA.

post_text: Spring is here! Please help the village by cleaning up on and around your property. We are asking that all residents and businesses sweep the sidewalks and curbs in front of your house or buildings. If you can't remove the piles of stones, our town man will be around to pick those up. Thank you all for your help in making our village beautiful!!

Wren Garden Club is now working on their 2015 Club Fundraiser.

Garden Club is again selling 5 gallon buckets of liquid laundry detergent for the cost of $45. Projects they have done and keep up with is... Landscaping on the Log House at Wren Park, bench and planter at Wren Library, Landscaping at Harrison Township Building.

Please help them to continue these projects that are occurring around the Wren Community. Orders are due Feb. 18th Please contact Michele Young at 419.910.0722

post_text:
Trick-or Treat time in Wren!

When: Saturday, November 1st from 4-6pm

At 6:15, after trick-or-treating, there will be a costume parade and contest with prizes. We hope you and your families are able to attend. We will post more details on the Wren Ballpark Association Facebook page as the event draws closer.

If you live in Wren, and are willing to participate, please turn on your porch light with treats ready for our ghosts, ghouls, goblins, super heroes, princesses, and ninjas. If you are in the decorating mood...the scarier the better!

WREN NEWS:
Friday, Oct. 10th is the last day to purchase WCS Chicken Dinner tickets. See any member for tickets.

The Wren Village Council meeting will be held on Monday, Oct. 13th at 7 pm at the Wren Town Hall. The meetings are open to the public.

Friends of Wren are sponsoring a Gun Raffle to benefit the Village of Wren. Tickets are $10 each. First prize is a Sig Sauer 1911 .45; second prize is a Sig Sauer .380; third prize is a Ruger Syn SS 10-22 50th Anniversary; fourth prize is 235 rounds of .22 cal LP ammo. Call 937-620-4903 for ticket info. Drawing will be held when all tickets are sold.

post_text:
The Wren Christmas Society is selling tickets for chicken dinners for Saturday, October 18, 2014. The food will be prepared by Gibson's Barnyard BBQ. The meal will include: 1/2 chicken, green beans, cheesy potatoes and a roll. Meals are by pre-sale tickets only.

Tickets are $8 each and are available for purchase now from any Wren Christmas Society member.

Dinners will be available for pick-up at the WCS building at the Wren Ballpark on Saturday, Oct. 18th between 11 am - 1 pm.

The money raised will be used to pay for the electricity for the Christmas lights this holiday season.
